10. What is the purpose of the WHEN condition in the trigger?
--------------------------------------------------------------
The WHEN condition is used in row-level triggers to specify when the trigger should execute.
The trigger will run only if the condition is TRUE.
Example
CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER salary_check
BEFORE UPDATE ON employees
FOR EACH ROW
WHEN (NEW.salary < 0)
BEGIN
   RAISE_APPLICATION_ERROR(-20001,'Salary cannot be negative');
END;
/
✅ The trigger runs only if salary becomes negative.
