14. Tell the importance of %TYPE and %ROWTYPE data types in PL/SQL.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
%TYPE
%TYPE is used to declare a variable with the same datatype as a table column.
Example
DECLARE
   v_salary employees.salary%TYPE;
BEGIN
   NULL;
END;
/
Here v_salary gets the same datatype as salary column.
%ROWTYPE
%ROWTYPE is used to store an entire row of a table.
Example
DECLARE
   emp_rec employees%ROWTYPE;
BEGIN
   SELECT * INTO emp_rec
   FROM employees
   WHERE emp_id = 1;
END;
/
15. What are the differences between ROLLBACK and ROLLBACK TO statements in PL/SQL?
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ROLLBACK	ROLLBACK TO
Undo all changes in transaction	Undo changes up to a SAVEPOINT
Transaction ends	Transaction continues
Example
SAVEPOINT sp1;
UPDATE employees SET salary=50000 WHERE emp_id=1;
ROLLBACK TO sp1;
